{"type":"user","uuid":"ec34f65c-da7d-4ef5-9cf3-25cded3ea8f4","session_id":"685aae5c-4106-4f0c-bd73-75d3c81ac2d9","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde3093cd6b4417e8ff108fc6029e","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `prizmkit analyze` CLI command isn't available yet. I'll perform the cross-check analysis manually using the 6 detection channels as specified in the reviewer agent workflow.\n\n---\n\n# 🔍 F-002 Cross-Document Consistency Analysis Report\n\n## Detection Channel Results\n\n### 1. 重复检测\n| Status | Finding |\n|--------|---------|\n| ✅ PASS | No significant redundancy detected. Command definitions in plan.md appropriately reference spec.md. |\n\n### 2. 歧义检测\n| Status | Finding |\n|--------|---------|\n| ⚠️ LOW | D1 decision states `/planner` defaults `type=planner` but spec.md doesn't clarify if this is implicit behavior or requires user action. |\n\n### 3. 不完整检测\n\n| # | Level | File:Line | Description |\n|---|-------|-----------|-------------|\n| 3.1 | **HIGH** | tasks.md:136 | **Missing task for US-6 (Error Guidance)**. T-105 is labeled `[US-6]` but implements planner handler, not error guidance. US-6 requires error message formatting (validator, formatter per plan.md:438). |\n| 3.2 | **HIGH** | tasks.md:17-68 | **Missing explicit task label for US-7 (Authorization Guard)**. plan.md:439 maps US-7 → T-010, but T-010 in tasks.md has no `[US-7]` label. Authorization guard is critical per US-7 acceptance criteria. |\n\n### 4. Prizm 规则对齐\n| Status | Finding |\n|--------|---------|\n| ✅ PASS | All file paths follow project structure. Module dependencies align with MODULE_INDEX. |\n\n### 5. 覆盖缺口\n\n| # | Level | File:Line | Description |\n|---|-------|-----------|-------------|\n| 5.1 | **CRITICAL** | spec.md:134-144, plan.md:429-439 | **`/planner` command has no User Story**. Command Reference (spec.md:140) defines `/planner` with subcommands run/status/logs, but no US exists for it. plan.md User Story Mapping has no entry for `/planner`. |\n| 5.2 | **HIGH** | spec.md:147-156, tasks.md | **No task for alias testing**. Alias Mapping defines `/p`, `/b`, `/s`, `/l` but no task explicitly tests alias resolution. T-901 (parser tests) may cover this, but not explicitly stated. |\n| 5.3 | **MEDIUM** | spec.md:101-115 (NFR-3), tasks.md | **No performance verification task**. NFR-3 requires \"命令解析 < 50ms\" but no task validates this constraint. |\n\n### 6. 不一致性\n\n| # | Level | File:Line | Description |\n|---|-------|-----------|-------------|\n| 6.1 | **CRITICAL** | tasks.md:136 vs plan.md:438 | **T-105 label mismatch**. tasks.md labels T-105 as `[US-6]` but implements planner handler. plan.md maps US-6 → \"validator, formatter \\| T-105\" (Error Guidance). These are completely different features. |\n| 6.2 | **HIGH** | plan.md:256-269 vs tasks.md:136 | **`/planner` aliases discrepancy**. plan.md:259 defines `aliases: []` for planner (empty), but no alias is mentioned in spec.md Alias Mapping either. This is consistent but `/planner` should arguably have an alias for consistency. |\n| 6.3 | **MEDIUM** | spec.md:145-156 vs plan.md:217-296 | **Alias `/b` maps to `/bugfix`**. Both spec.md and plan.md agree. However, spec.md lists 4 aliases while plan.md command definitions include additional aliases (e.g., `aliases: [s]` for status at line 276). ✅ Actually consistent - rechecked. |\n\n---\n\n## Summary of CRITICAL/HIGH Findings\n\n| ID | Level | Issue | Fix Recommendation |\n|----|-------|-------|---------------------|\n| **5.1** | **CRITICAL** | `/planner` command has no User Story in spec.md | Add US-8 for Planner Command, or clarify that `/planner` is covered under US-1 Pipeline Command (as a pipeline type variant per D1) |\n| **6.1** | **CRITICAL** | T-105 label mismatch — labeled [US-6] but implements planner, not error guidance | 1. Rename current T-105 to T-106, label as `[Planner]` not `[US-6]`<br>2. Create new T-105 labeled `[US-6]` for error formatter implementation<br>3. Update plan.md User Story Mapping to include planner task reference |\n| **3.1** | **HIGH** | No task for US-6 (Error Guidance) implementation | Add explicit task for error message formatter (T-105 or new T-105a) that implements user-friendly error messages per US-6 acceptance criteria |\n| **3.2** | **HIGH** | US-7 not labeled in T-010 | Add `[US-7]` label to T-010 task description to ensure authorization guard is traceable |\n| **5.2** | **HIGH** | No explicit alias testing task | Add test case in T-901 acceptance criteria: \"Alias resolution for /p, /b, /s, /l tested\" |\n\n---\n\n## Verdict\n\n| Indicator | Value |\n|-----------|-------|\n| CRITICAL Issues | **2** |\n| HIGH Issues | **3** |\n| MEDIUM Issues | **2** |\n| LOW Issues | **1** |\n| **Judgment** | ⛔ **NEEDS FIXES** |\n\n---\n\n## COMPLETION_SIGNAL\n\n```\nCOMPLETION_SIGNAL\nAgent: Reviewer\nFeature: F-002 (002-telegram-pipeline-command-router)\nPhase: 4 (Cross-check Analysis)\nJudgment: NEEDS_FIXES\nCritical_Count: 2\nHigh_Count: 3\nAction_Required: Report to Coordinator → Return to PM for fix\n```\n\n---\n\n### 📤 ISSUE_REPORT → Coordinator\n\n**Issue 1 (CRITICAL)**: `/planner` command defined in Command Reference but has no User Story\n- **Files**: spec.md:140, plan.md:256-269\n- **Impact**: Traceability gap — feature has no acceptance criteria\n\n**Issue 2 (CRITICAL)**: T-105 task label mismatch with plan.md mapping\n- **Files**: tasks.md:136 vs plan.md:438\n- **Impact**: Implementation may miss Error Guidance (US-6) functionality\n\n---\n\n**Recommendation**: Return to PM for spec/tasks alignment before Dev implementation. The 2 CRITICAL issues must be resolved to ensure:\n1. All commands have traceable User Stories\n2. Task labels accurately reflect User Story assignments\n\n[Agent ID: agent-34b28537]"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde3093cd6b4417e8ff108fc6029e","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T18:38:44.025Z","_requestId":"8512c899584843ddbcfa3594c4781204"}
